    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA153-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai melinta talaivi (ET: tōḻikkuc) colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said who was weakened in the time of marriage.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA153">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kuṇakaṭaṉ mukantu kuṭakkēr piruḷi</l>
<l>            maṇṭiṇi ñālam viḷaṅkak kammiyar</l>
<l>            cempucori pāṉaiyiṉ miṉṉiyev vāyun</l>
<l>            taṉṟoḻil vāytta viṉkura leḻili</l>
<l>            teṉpula maruṅkiṟ ceṉṟaṟ ṟāṅku </l>
<l>            neñca mavarvayiṟ ceṉṟeṉa vīṇṭoḻin</l>
<l>            tuṇṭa laḷitte ṉuṭampē viṟaṟpōr</l>
<l>            veñciṉa vēntaṉ pakaiyalaik kalaṅki</l>
<l>            vāḻvōr pōkiya pērūrp</l>
<l>            pāḻkāt tirunta taṉimakaṉ pōṉṟē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent2">Because [my] heart has gone to him</l>
<l>– like the sweet-voiced cloud, that has achieved its task everywhere(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">evvāy-um</term>: T.V.G. explains this as an adverb of place ("at whatever place") which is not backed up by the TL (which does not even give "place" among the meaning of <term xml:lang="ta">vāy</term>), but nevertheless conceivable and plausible in the context.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent2">drawing [water] from the eastern sea, rising [and] darkening to the west,</l>
<l rend="indent2">[and] flashing like a polished(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">coli</term> is explained by T.V.G. here as "to polish", which gives a beautiful image, but is once more not to be found in the TL. If we want to adhere to the dictionary we will have to read: "like a pot from which the artisans pour forth [molten] copper" - which is likewise conceivable.</note> pot of copper [made] by artisans,</l>
<l rend="indent2">so that the world firm of soil shines,</l>
<l rend="indent">goes to the southern fields [and] subsides –</l>
<l>my body is pitiful in staying behind here [and] eating,</l>
<l rend="indent">like a single man who stays protecting the ruins</l>
<l rend="indent2">of a big village from which the inhabitants have gone,</l>
<l rend="indent3">agitated by the oppression of enmity from a king in hot anger,</l>
<l rend="indent4">in victorious battle.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
